- title "Simple Blog Post app using Formtastic"
%h2 This is a quick demo including:
%ul
  %li 
    Nifty-Generators:
    %a{:target=>'blank',  :href=>'http://github.com/ryanb/nifty-generators'} http://github.com/ryanb/nifty-generators
  %li 
    Formtastic:
    %a{:target=>'blank',  :href=>'http://github.com/justinfrench/formtastic'} http://github.com/justinfrench/formtastic
  %li 
    Haml markup:
    %a{:target=>'blank',  :href=>'http://haml-lang.com/'} http://haml-lang.com/
    %a{:target=>'blank',  :href=>'http://haml-lang.com/try.html'} TryHaml
  %li
    %a{:target=>'blank',  :href=>'http://sass-lang.com/'} Sass stylesheet framework
  %li 
    An awesome sass stylesheet specifically for formtastic:
    %a{:target=>'blank',  :href =>'http://github.com/activestylus/formtastic-sass'} http://github.com/activestylus/formtastic-sass
  %li
    with some
    %a{:target=>'blank',  :href =>'http://jquery.com/'} jQuery
  %li
    Deployed on
    %a{:target=>'blank',  :href =>'http://www.heroku.com'} Heroku
    with the
    %a{:target=>'blank',  :href => 'http://blog.heroku.com/archives/2009/8/18/heroku_sass/'} heroku_sass plugin
    to manage the compiled files


%table
  %tr
    %th Title
    %th Body
    %th Category
    %th Live
  - for post in @posts
    %tr
      %td= h post.title
      %td= h post.body
      %td= h post.category
      %td= h post.live
      %td= link_to 'Show', post
      %td= link_to 'Edit', edit_post_path(post)
      %td= link_to 'Destroy', post, :confirm => 'Are you sure?', :method => :delete

%p= link_to "New Post", new_post_path
